The rule described means every time left-shift, then add the number

```
number = 1, string = 1
number = 2, string left shift 2 bits = 100, adds number 2 becomes 110
number = 3, string left shift 2 bits = 11000, adds number 3 beomces 11011
...
```

The technique is to use bit-wise operation to find number of digits for the number, then do left-sift and add number. Also, add number mean bit-wise operation `or`.

update at 1/28, original code find digits is not efficient, change to new one

```golang
func concatenatedBinary(n int) int {
	num, digits := 1, 1
	var ans int
	mod := int(1e9 + 7)

	for ; num <= n; num++ {
        if num == 1 << digits {
			digits++
		}

		ans = ans << digits
		ans |= num

		ans = ans % mod
	}

	return ans
}
```

