Let f(n) = concatenation of binary numbers from 1 to n
So we need to find f(n)

We append the numbers from 1 to n one by one in a loop.
To find f(i),
	we left shift the f(i-1) by number of bits in i, and add i to it
	then we take the mod

**eg.** n = 4
f(1) = 1
	f(2) = 1<<(number of bits in 2) + 2 = 1<<2 + 2 = 100 + 10 = 110
	f(3) = 11<<(number of bits in 3) + 3 = 11<<2 + 3 = 11000 + 11 = 11011
	f(4) = 1011<<(number of bits in 4) + 4 = 11011<< 3 + 4 = 11011000 + 100 = 11011100
(also taking mod 1e9+7 simultaneously in each step to avoid overflow)

```
#define MOD 1000000007
class Solution {
public:
    int concatenatedBinary(int n) {
        long long ans = 0;
        for(long long i=1; i<=n; i++) {
            ans = ((ans << ((int)floor(log2(i)) + 1)) + i)%MOD;
        }
        return ans;
    }
};
```

