Trick is to add left shift of previous number formed till now by the size of binary string formed by the present number(Place Value) and then adding the present number.

Doing left shift by size 'sz' is equivalent to multiplying by 'sz'th power of 2.
Size of strings can be updated whenever we hit powers of 2.
do take mod(1e9+7) whenever possible inorder to avoid overflows.
```
class Solution {
public:
    int concatenatedBinary(int n) {
        int ans=0,sz=0;
        for(int i=1;i<=n;i++){
            if(i==(1<<sz))sz++;// increments whenever we hit next power of 2
            ans=((ans*1LL*(1<<sz))%md+i)%md; // left shift previous number formed then add i, then take mod
        }
        return ans;
    }
};
```
