solutions.content:
First of all, the number of left-shifts is the number of `2` we need to multiply.

For instance, when `n = 3`,
* It is `1`, `10`, and `11`.
* We start with `1`, and we left-shift 2 positions after we add `10`, which get us `110`  `= ` `1 * 2 * 2 + 2 = 6`.
* And then we left-shift two positions again after we add `11`, which give us `11011` `=` `6 * 2 * 2 + 3 = 27`.

```
    private static int MOD = 1000000007;

    public int concatenatedBinary(int n) {
        long ans = 0;
        int highest = 2;
        for (int i = 1; i <= n; i++) {
            if (i >= highest) {
                highest *= 2;
            }
            ans = (ans * highest + i) % MOD;
        }
        return (int) ans;
    }
```

